OL,6,FIt said turnout for the ballot was
OL,7,F55.3%, down from the previous few
OL,8,Fyears, which meant that with 90.05% in
OL,9,Ffavour, that means only 49.78% voted
OL,10,Fin favour of strike action.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for the department
OL,13,Fsaid: "While most resident doctors in
OL,14,Fthe BMA did not vote to strike, it is
OL,15,Fdisappointing that the BMA is
OL,16,Fcontinuing to threaten strike action
OL,17,Fafter a pay rise of 28.9% over the
OL,18,Flast three years.
