OL,4,Cstrike over pay offer
OL,6,FStreeting previously awarded doctors a
OL,7,F22% pay increase spread over two
OL,8,Fyears. At the time, doctors accepted
OL,9,Fthis offer but warned they would want
OL,10,Fmore in the coming years to keep their
OL,11,Fpay at competitive levels and above
OL,12,Finflation.
OL,14,FGovernment data suggests ending these
OL,15,Fdisputes saved around half a million
OL,16,Fappointments and operations from being
OL,17,Fcancelled and cut waiting lists at the
OL,18,Ftime by 193,000.
