OL,4,Cstrike over pay offer
OL,6,FThe BMA says that if the current deal,
OL,7,Fwhich amounts to a 5.4% increase, was
OL,8,Foffered in perpetuity, it would take
OL,9,F12 years to reach the real-terms level
OL,10,Fof their members' pay in 2008.
OL,12,FCommenting on the government's
OL,13,Fcommitment to meeting this goal, the
OL,14,FBMA wrote: "As part of last year's
OL,15,Fdeal, the government pledged to work
OL,16,Fwith us to make medicine an attractive
OL,17,Fand rewarding career choice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/16
